  "patient_summary": "Olivia is a 73-year-old female with a medical history including Hyperlipidemia associated with Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus, Mixed dyslipidemia, and Essential Hypertension. She has also experienced Postoperative anemia and Leg Pain. Notable past infections include MRSA in September 2020 (resolved March 2023) and COVID-19 in January 2021 (recovered January 2021). She underwent a Colonoscopy with Biopsy in February 2025. Laboratory results from July 2023 indicated elevated Ferritin and Glucose, with low Iron and Iron Saturation, consistent with potential iron deficiency despite high ferritin. Her blood pressure was 128/78 in January 2025, meeting her goal of <140/90. She has various in-home monitoring goals for diabetes management, including diet, medication adherence, and blood sugar checks, with a personal goal to get off insulin. Her functional status indicates no difficulty hearing, adequate vision, but serious difficulty walking or climbing stairs."
